This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with the design of neural networks. Additionally, it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the use of domain knowledge to guide the network design. The paper also mentions the application of the furcated network architecture in computer vision (cs.CV) and chemical engineering (cs.CE), which are other possible sub-categories. Lastly, the paper discusses the distillation of design principles (cs.SD), which could also be a relevant sub-category.
